<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1307" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1307">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/59.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Consul <persName type="to">Hostetter</persName>.</hi><note n="104" xml:id="d1307fn104">Same to the Consular officers at Nogales and Log
                                Mochis.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Reported to Department that Constitutionalists are threatening forced
                            loan upon Almacla Sugar Refineries Company, American corporation owning
                            large properties at Navolato near Culiacan.</p>
                        <p>Make protest to Constitutionalist leaders against imposition of this
                            loan.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>